# Disco Limerick

There once was a man who would dance,
In his bell-bottoms, giving a glance.
    The disco ball spun,
    As he had his fun,
And the ladies all fell in a trance.

His moves were electric and bold,
With sequences perfectly scrolled.
    "Stayin' Alive" was his jam,
    Never once gave a damn,
As his story on dance floors was told.

When the music would thump through the night,
His platform shoes gleamed in the light.
    The king of the floor,
    Always leaving them sore,
As disco fever reached its height.

