**Disco Delight**  

There once was a dance floor so bright,  
Where folks boogied all through the night.  
With mirror balls high,  
They’d shake to the sky—  
Oh, what a dazzling sight!  

The bass line was funky and tight,  
As dancers spun left and then right.  
In platform shoes tall,  
They grooved through it all,  
Under glittering strobe lights so white.  

But when the last record took flight,  
The crowd sighed, "Man, this ain't right!"  
Yet disco lives on,  
From dusk until dawn—  
A groove that just won’t say goodnight!

